President Obama and Prime Minister Erdogan of Turkey had a phone call to discuss coordinating efforts to accelerate a political transition in Syria. They expressed concerns about the Syrian regime's attacks on its own people and the deteriorating humanitarian conditions in the country. They pledged to assist displaced Syrians within Syria, Turkey, and the broader region. The President acknowledged Turkey's generosity in hosting Syrian refugees. The two leaders agreed to remain in close contact to promote a democratic transition in Syria. Prime Minister Erdogan also offered his condolences for the tragedy in Colorado.